The Senate has confirmed the nomination of Dr. Mahmuda Isah as Resident Electoral Commissioner (REC) of the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC). The resolution of the Upper Chamber followed its consideration and adoption of the report of the Committee on INEC that screened the nominee. The report was presented by Senator Sadiq Umar (APC – Kwara North) on behalf of the Chairman of the Committee, Senator Kabiru Gaya. The committees observed that Isah had satisfied the requirements of section 154(1),Section 14 (1) and (2) of the Third Schedule, Part 1F of the constitution and orders 119 and 121 of the Senate standing orders, 2015 as (amended). The Committee recommended that the nominee be confirmed. Read Also ; Senate congratulates President-Elect Tinubu In his contribution, Senator Barau Jibrin (APC – Kano North) said: “Permit me to commend the Committee for conducting a thorough exercise in order to confirm this nominee. The report has clearly shown that the nominee keeps a clean record. “For this reason, I urge my colleagues without any delay to give the nod for the nominee to be confirmed.” Senators approved that the nominee be confirmed when the recommendation was put to voice vote by Senate President Ahmad Lawan. END